content.text:
Ah! Now I see the problem. Let me show you what your boss means:

## What Your Boss Is Saying

You added **267 CSS variables** to `design-system.css`. That's WAY too many. Here's why he said **"I wouldn't add all these CSS variables myself"**:

### Problem 1: Full Color Scales (Unnecessary)

```css
/* You added 11 shades for EVERY color */
--color-primary-50: oklch(95% 0.03 200);
--color-primary-100: oklch(90% 0.05 200);
--color-primary-200: oklch(80% 0.08 200);
--color-primary-300: oklch(70% 0.11 200);
--color-primary-400: oklch(60% 0.14 200);
--color-primary-500: oklch(50% 0.16 200);  /* Base */
--color-primary-600: oklch(45% 0.14 200);
--color-primary-700: oklch(35% 0.11 200);
--color-primary-800: oklch(25% 0.08 200);
--color-primary-900: oklch(15% 0.05 200);
--color-primary-950: oklch(10% 0.03 200);

/* Then did this for: success, warning, error, info, neutral = 55+ variables just for colors! */
```

**Boss's point:** You don't need to manually define all these. **Tailwind already does this!**

### Problem 2: Animation Variables (Redundant)

```css
--animation-fade-in: fadeIn var(--transition-base);
--animation-fade-out: fadeOut var(--transition-base);
--animation-slide-in-up: slideInUp var(--transition-medium) var(--ease-out);
--animation-slide-in-down: slideInDown var(--transition-medium) var(--ease-out);
/* etc... */
```

**Boss's point:** Just use `@keyframes` directly. No need for variables wrapping animations.

### Problem 3: Excessive Spacing Variables

```bash
# You have 24 spacing variables
--spacing-0, --spacing-1, --spacing-2, ... --spacing-96
```

**Boss's point:** Tailwind already has `p-4`, `m-8`, `gap-6`. Why duplicate?

---

## What Your Boss WOULD Add (Minimal Approach)

```css
/* design-system.css - MINIMAL VERSION */
@layer base {
  :root {
    /* ============================================
     * BRAND COLORS (Just the base values)
     * ============================================ */
    --color-primary: #007c89;
    --color-success: #10b981;
    --color-warning: #f59e0b;
    --color-error: #ef4444;
    --color-info: #3b82f6;

    /* ============================================
     * SURFACE COLORS (Light mode)
     * ============================================ */
    --surface-primary: #ffffff;
    --surface-secondary: #f9fafb;
    --surface-tertiary: #f3f4f6;

    /* ============================================
     * TEXT COLORS
     * ============================================ */
    --text-primary: #111827;
    --text-secondary: #6b7280;
    --text-tertiary: #9ca3af;

    /* ============================================
     * SHADOWS (Just what you actually use)
     * ============================================ */
    --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px 0 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.05);
    --shadow-md: 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
    --shadow-lg: 0 10px 15px -3px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);

    /* ============================================
     * TRANSITIONS (Just durations & easings)
     * ============================================ */
    --transition-fast: 150ms;
    --transition-base: 300ms;
    --transition-slow: 500ms;

    --ease-out: cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1);
    --ease-bounce: cubic-bezier(0.68, -0.55, 0.265, 1.55);
  }

  /* Dark mode overrides */
  [data-theme="dark"] {
    --surface-primary: #0f172a;
    --surface-secondary: #1e293b;
    --surface-tertiary: #334155;

    --text-primary: #f1f5f9;
    --text-secondary: #cbd5e1;
    --text-tertiary: #94a3b8;
  }
}
```

**That's it! ~30 variables instead of 267.**

---

## Why This Approach Is Better

### ❌ Your Approach (267 variables):
```vue
<template>
  <!-- Have to remember custom variable names -->
  <div class="bg-[var(--color-primary-500)] text-[var(--text-primary)]">
    Content
  </div>
</template>
```

### ✅ Boss's Approach (30 variables):
```vue
<template>
  <!-- Use Tailwind's built-in scale -->
  <div class="bg-teal-500 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">
    Content
  </div>

  <!-- Only use custom variables for brand/surface colors -->
  <div class="bg-[var(--surface-primary)]">
    Content
  </div>
</template>
```

---

## What Your Boss Means by "I Wouldn't Add These Myself"

He means:

1. **Don't duplicate Tailwind's built-in scales**
   - Tailwind has `gray-50` through `gray-950` → Don't create `--color-neutral-50` through `--color-neutral-950`
   - Tailwind has spacing → Don't create `--spacing-1` through `--spacing-96`

2. **Only add variables for things Tailwind CAN'T handle**
   - Brand-specific surface colors (`--surface-primary`)
   - Dark mode semantic colors (`--text-primary`)
   - Custom shadows you use everywhere
   - Transition durations you reuse

3. **Keep it minimal**
   - If you only use 5 shadows, define 5, not 10
   - If you only use 3 transition speeds, define 3, not 8

4. **Let Tailwind do the heavy lifting**
   - Use `bg-teal-500` not `bg-[var(--color-primary-500)]`
   - Use `p-4` not `padding: var(--spacing-4)`

---

## Practical Example

### ❌ Over-engineered (Your PR):
```css
/* 267 variables */
--color-primary-500: oklch(50% 0.16 200);
--spacing-4: 1rem;
--animation-fade-in: fadeIn var(--transition-base);
```

```vue
<div class="p-[var(--spacing-4)] bg-[var(--color-primary-500)]"
     style="animation: var(--animation-fade-in)">
  Content
</div>
```

### ✅ Simplified (What Boss Wants):
```css
/* ~30 variables */
--surface-primary: #ffffff;
--transition-base: 300ms;
```

```vue
<div class="p-4 bg-teal-500 animate-fade-in">
  Content
</div>
```

**The @keyframes are in CSS, Tailwind provides the utility classes, and you only need variables for brand/semantic colors.**

---

## Summary

**Your boss is saying:**
- "Tailwind already has a complete design system built-in (colors, spacing, shadows)"
- "Don't reinvent it with 267 custom variables"
- "Only add variables for project-specific things Tailwind doesn't know about"
- "Keep it to ~20-40 variables max, not 267"

**Makes sense?**

# Ultra-Specific Execution Plan

## Phase 1: Audit & Analyze (Understand Current State)

### Step 1.1: Audit CSS Variable Usage
```bash
# Find all files using custom CSS variables
grep -r "var(--" src/ --include="*.vue" --include="*.css" --include="*.astro" > /tmp/css-var-usage.txt

# Count usage of each variable
grep -oh "var(--[a-zA-Z0-9-]*)" src/ -r | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn > /tmp/css-var-frequency.txt
```

**Goal:** Identify which of the 267 variables are actually used vs unused bloat

**Expected outcome:**
